laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is mildly dilated measuring up to 8 mm with a mildly thick and enhancing wall. There is mild periappendiceal fat stranding. No free air or free fluid. No focal fluid collection is noted. The liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesion. The spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically, without hydronephrosis.
